XSAN is a Storage Area Network solution by Apple.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Version 0.3	- 2012-06-27 - Arvinder Singh (http://twitter.com/askang)
Version 0.2	- 2012-06-27 - Arvinder Singh (http://twitter.com/askang)
Version 0.1	- 2012-06-27 - Arvinder Singh (http://twitter.com/askang)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

xsanctl command [arg [...]]
===========================
help 			: Display a list of the available xsanctl commands
ping 			: `ping' xsand. Used to verify that xsand is responsive.
mount volumeName 	: Mounts the volume volumeName.  Then auto-mount at startup.
unmount volumeName 	: Unmounts the volume volumeName.
list 			: Lists the volumes available on the SAN and mounted path.
sanConfigChanged 	: Notify Xsan that SAN conf changed and should be reloaded.
roleChanged 		: Notify Xsan that role of this computer has changed/removed.
disksChanged 		: Notify Xsan that disks have changed and should be rescanned.

Configuration files (/Library/Filesystems/Xsan/config)
======================================================
volume.cfg		: Volume settings
volume-auxdata.plist	: Additional volume settings used by Xsan Admin
fsmlist			: Volume autostart list
fsnameservers		: Controller list
automount.plist		: Xsan volumes auto mounts and their mount options
config.plist		: Private Xsan Admin configuration information
notification.plist	: Notification settings made with Xsan Admin
notes/		: Note files whose contents were entered in Admin Inspector window
uuid			: Private Xsan Admin computer identification information
license.dat		: File to place StorNext licenses if add StorNext clients
.auth_secret		: Shared secret file used when adding StorNext clients to your SAN

Management
==========
cvmkdir 	: Create an Xsan Directory with an Affinity
snfsdefrag	: move files to new storage pool after changing an affinity
cvfail	: sends out email notification configured in XSAN Admin

cvadmin 	: View or change volume and storage pool settings
cvaffinity 	: Manipulate affinity tags manually 
cvcp 		: Copy files or folders 
cvfsck 	: Check or repair a volume 
cvlabel 	: View, label, and initialize LUNs
cvmkdir 	: Create a folder and assign an affinity
cvmkfile 	: Create and preallocate a file
cvmkfs 	: Initialize a volume
cvupdatefs 	: Apply volume setup changes
snfsdefrag 	: Defragment a volume
xsanctl 	: Mount and unmount Xsan volumes
Glossery
========
fsmpm		: File System Manager port mapper daemon. Both on server and client.
fsm			: File System Manager daemon. Server daemon manages XSAN volume.</pre></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="footer">Powered by <a href="http://www.sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a>,
